Set Up a Local Git Repository 
Step 1: Install Git
        Download Git 

Verify Installation
        git --version

Step 2: Create and Initialize a Git Repository

        cd C:\Users\YourName\Documents\MyWebsite

        Initialize a Git repository in this folder:

        git init

Step 3: Add and Commit Files

        Commit the files with a message:

        git commit -m "Initial commit - Static website"
Step 4: Track Changes

        git status
        git log
Step 5: Ignore Unwanted Files (Optional)

        echo node_modules/ > .gitignore
        echo *.log >> .gitignore

âœ… Git is now tracking your static website!
You can track changes, revert versions, and collaborate easily.
